    About Us

    Exhaust System Cleaning Expert

    Hao Hao Cleaning Company has over 10 years of experiences of high temperature power wash for commercial flue exhaust system. We are licensed and insured company. We has specialty licensed by both New York City and Nassau County in Long Island, and can provide certified label by NYC and Nassau County. Our cleaning service are high quality and satisfaction guaranteed. we guarantee to pass all inspections from Fire Marshall after the cleaning service. Our services cover all sizes of restaurants, food courts, food trucks, etc. Contact us and we are here to help.

    Cleaning Services We Provided

    What We Provide

    100% Pass the inspection from Fire Marshall Guaranteed

    We guarantee you will pass the inspection from your local Fire Marshall after our cleaning service or your money back.

    Professional Management

    All sizes restaurants hood and flue exhaust system clean

    We are using high pressure steam power washer to clean your flue exhaust system and kitchen hood. We are using special made chemical remove dirt and grease. 100% guaranteed our clients will pass the inspection from local Fire Marshall or your moeny back.

    Other Cooking Equipment Clean

    Our cleaning service also covers other equipment that catches the grease and will cause the fires if they stay dirty. The equipment including Deep Fryer, Stove Stand, Griller, Range Ring, Wall against range, Pipe inside cook area, Oven, your restaurant floor and Range oven. Contact us for the whole service plan.

    Exhuast Fans and Blower Clean

    We can also clean your exhaust fans and blower. Our team will climb to your roof to perform the services.

    Filters Clean

    For your convenience, filters can be also cleaned at the time of service. So you don't need to change your filter later on and can call for inspection right the way.

    We will manage and keep your account in file and send you a reminder per NYS/NYC fire code requirements and perform the cleaning service for you before the service label expiration date. You don't need to remember and ever need to worry about your service expiration and get in trouble from your Fire Department.
